solution.p:
(c) Compare \lambda to the smallest dimensions of the plate, which would be the square-root of the area, \sqrt{A}.  Note, we cannot compare a length to an area, that is why we must get the square root of the area. Here 


	 \lambda \amp = \frac{3\times 10^8\:\textrm{m/s}}{10^9\:\textrm{Hz}} = 0.3\:\textrm{m}
	 sqrt{A} = 3 \text{ m}


Therefore, we have \lambda \lt \lt \sqrt{A}, we can use the ray approximation if we do not need intensity studies.
